description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM/SECONDMENT FOR 6 MONTHS DUE TO THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN APPLYING FOR THE SECONDMENT POSITION, YOU MUST OBTAIN PERMISSION FROM YOUR CURRENT LINE MANAGER PRIOR TO APPLYING FOR THIS POST. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a band 6 Mental Health Nurse to join our busy CMHT which covers the large geographical area of the Cynon Valley.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced, enthusiastic and committed mental health nurse who will undertake the role of Care Coordinator for adults of working age who require support due to complex mental health needs. You will work in conjunction with health and Local Authority colleagues in the delivery of a quality and supportive mental health service under the framework of the Mental Health Measures (2010) Wales.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work as part of the wider multi disciplinary team and develop close working relationships with other service providers, both community and hospital based, to ensure a smooth transition between services for the people you work with.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a community mental health nurse you will provide specialist knowledge and advice to a wide range of service users and providers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work autonomously but under indirect supervision of the CPN Team Leader. You will manage your own caseload effectively and will be expected to engage in regular caseload and practice supervision and also support the Team Leader to achieve organisational targets and improve service provision&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 11th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Matthew Ingram - CPN Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;matthew.ingram@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01443 715100&lt;/p&gt;
